<p>The iPad owners among the PLoS BLOGs readers can use the free
Flipboard application to read all the great content that is written by
my fellow ploggers PLoGsters (as suggested by
<ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://web.archive.org/web/20120604164119/http://blogs.plos.org/takeasdirected/2010/09/03/latest-from-the-plogsters">David
Kroll</ext-link>). In Flipboard simply create a new section and then add
content to it by following the @plosblogs Twitter account.</p>
<fig>
  <graphic mimetype="image" mime-subtype="jpeg" xlink:href="https://web.archive.org/web/20120604164119im_/http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4103/4959511883_06a51c32ce.jpg" xlink:title="" />
</fig>
<p>There are of course many other ways Flipboard can be used to follow
science blogs, e.g. by following the @researchblogs Twitter account.
More info can be found in
<ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://web.archive.org/web/20120604164119/http://blogs.nature.com/mfenner/2010/08/01/flipboard-changes-the-way-we-use-twitter">this
blog</ext-link> posts I wrote last month.</p>
